	After almost 2 years of entertainment, the king is almost mournful to hear the beast has been slayed.

	He knows very well that after the end of the war, the people had been twitchy. A common enemy always helped unite people. That and scandals. There have been a few scandals of course, but nothing worth paying attention to. Or at the very least nothing quite as interesting and as mysterious as a murderous beast which made his subjects bleed for almost 2 years. Really the hunt of the Beast of Gevaudan had been the most fun he’s had in ages. It almost made him consider joining the effort, almost. 

	As he stares at the stuffed Beast, he’s glad he didn't join. It's just a wolf. Sure, it is a bigger wolf than he’s ever seen. His royal servant told him the beast weighed 84 Kilograms. Still the king feels overjoyed by that kill, especially one made by his very own officer. But, that beast killed many and for about two years no one was able to put it down. Of course it was no match for his porte-arquebusier

	The king scrunches his noses in disgust as he inspects the beast.

