:: Tavern1 {"position":"5025,450","size":"100,100"}
Perhaps it is because you worked, or perhaps it is because you've had a rough night, but a huge part of you needs to see Lou. Before you even realize, your feet are heading to the Inn.

The Inn, La Lune Rousse, is, quite honestly the only part of town that makes it interesting, it's in the middle of the village, the village being a road? traveling? Sur la route?? Usually
Usually people go to have a drink once or twice a week, most people who go there are travelers who need a shelter for the night on their way to the next town.
Lou is the owner. Her aunt and uncle used to own the place with Lou only helping, but since they moved town they left the inn to Lou, who took over the establishment splendidly.

And while she rarely has time off, you often go meet her there to hang out. She always tries to make time for you.
Besides, she does give you sweet prices, being your closest friend and all.

When you enter, there's a few regulars there, you recognise the younglings Damien, Josephine and Louis who are as usual, drinking in the corner. There's old Charles, who after taking care of the fields, goes for one drink before heading home to his husband.

However your looks go straight to Lou, she's not prepping any meal, it's too early for any of that yet, but she is making drinks and serving folks.
She looks incredibly put together for someone who works at the inn, her curly ginger hair is tied into a loose bun, She smiles when she sees you, almost dazzling as always. She's always been one of those people that have the brightest smile. The smile falls on her face when she sees the state you're in. She's always been quite observant.

You head straight to “your” table. It doesn't really belong to you, but it's in the corner with your back against the wall, it allows you to spot everyone who comes in. Besides, it's a bit secluded so you quite enjoy that.

After serving Charles, she heads straight to your table and sit down in front of you.

“What's wrong?”

